bouilli
Homonym Number:  1
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:an old word for stewed meat preserved in a tin as a common fare in emigrant ships and early settlement; compare <i>bully beef</i>; bouilli tin; a usu. early 19C. spg of a usual emigrant commodity: tinned boiled or stewed meat, esp. beef (OED 17C.), often, as emigrant-ship, or early colonial fare, `soup and bouilli'. Now usually<i> bully-beef</i>.
